body.description: Tackle your next adventure with the Rightline Gear Range Jr car top and roof rack cargo carrier. Designed for use WITH or WITHOUT a roof rack, you can attach the straps of this roof cargo bag to your vehicle's roof rack or use the included car clips to attach the straps to a vehicle's door frame weather molding - the only revolutionary solution of its kind that WILL NOT interfere with passenger headroom. Rated Weatherproof +, the Range Jr's UV-protected PVC Semi-Coated Mesh XT shell, urethane-coated zipper, and hook-and-loop-close zipper flap provide a dual barrier from the elements. Featuring 10 cubic feet of rooftop storage, this compact car luggage carrier roof bag allows you to transport your cargo and your passengers without compromising on safety, comfort, or convenience. All Rightline Gear products come backed by a 1-year manufacturer's warranty, so Gear up with confidence!

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: What makes Rightline Gear Range Car Top Carriers Weatherproof +? A step up from Rightline Gear’s Ace Car Top Carriers, The Range Carriers add a urethane coated zipper. A zipper flap adds extra protection. All seams of the carrier are welded watertight and Rightline Gear’s proprietary PVC Semi-Coated Mesh XT stands up to the elements for years to come. Other carriers may claim to be waterproof or weatherproof, but they do not have the features to back it up.

Features Urethane Coated Zipper The Range Car Top Carriers use Urethane Coated Zippers as the first line of defense against moisture and the elements, while other carriers use standard zippers with exposed teeth that let water in! PVC Semi-Coated Mesh XT High velocities are no match for Range Car Top Carriers, thanks to their heavy-duty, Xtra Tough PVC Semi-Coated Mesh XT construction. Stuff Sack All of Rightline Gear's Range Car Top Carriers come with a handy stuff sack so your carrier is always on hand when you need it, and easily stows away when you don't.

Attachment Methods WITH a Roof Rack Loop the included straps around the roof rack side rails or cross bars. WITHOUT a Roof Rack - Car Clips Start with the Car Clips on the (4) attachment straps. Open the vehicle's doors and hook the Car Clips under the door frame weather molding.

Standard Airline Carry-on. Carrier Fit Guide To ensure a proper fit, please measure your vehicle's roof (as shown above) and compare to the carrier's dimensions. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reliable and Weatherproof Rooftop Luggage Carrier
reviews.reviewText: I recently embarked on a 2900-mile trip with the rooftop luggage carrier, and it exceeded my expectations. The zipper closure proved to be weatherproof, keeping my belongings safe and dry even during unexpected rain.The user-friendly design made installation a breeze, and the clear instructions ensured a hassle-free setup. What impressed me most was its performance in adverse weather conditions – it worked like a charm in the rain, maintaining its waterproof seal.After the long journey, the rooftop carrier still looks as good as new, a testament to its durability. I highly recommend the carrier for its reliability, ease of use, and impressive weather resistance. It truly made my road trip worry-free.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I was worried about using this carrier because I'd never used one before and there were some poor reviews, but I'm so glad I bought it! It turned out to be a lifesaver. It's incredibly sturdy, so much so that I had difficulty unfolding it out of the box. The material is thick and a bit stiff at first use.The carrier isn't heavy at all but it took a bit of muscling to get it packed because the material is stiff. I was able to load/unload the carrier on top of my car by myself using a stepladder.The straps and attachments were strong and the directions were easy to follow. I double knotted the straps and checked them when I stopped for gas, no issues with loosening or slipping.The first trip I made with the carrier was 600 miles with sunny, slightly windy weather. The carrier didn't impact my speed or gas mileage much. The second trip, 300 miles, was in pouring rain. No leaks, everything was perfectly dry!This carrier was a great buy, I'm so glad I got it! It made my move a lot less stressful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this item for a long distance travel it seemed sketchy at first. But after traveling from Florida to California with it attached to my car. I gotta say it’s sturdy the quality of this product is insane and works well and lots of storage inside of it. Id definitely would recommend this to my friends and family who are traveling and need space to store things either for a camping trip or long distance travel

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Definitely Durable and Waterproof
reviews.reviewText: Just finished 2nd trip with it and drove thru rain and sat outside for a night in the rain. We fit most all out camping stuff in it ( 2 tents, sleeping bag, stove, 3 life jackets, etc). I was impressed with how much fit in it If packed just right. I would suggest packing the front with a slight angle up for wind. AND, twist the straps 2-3 turns to cut the noise/vibration.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked fine. Support was responsive.
reviews.reviewText: Used to expand on what my KIA Soul could carry. It added 10 cubic feet. The video showed me how to install without having a roof rack. Trip was around 275 miles each way. There was no rain during either direction. Once you’ve tightened the straps down make sure to tie a knot with the excess strap near the buckle. Rightline support said I could have gone with a 15 cubic foot product or a ten. But when I specified my car and model with Amazon it overrode my preference and insisted the 15 was not right for my vehicle. Well built. I used a car roof protector upon which to place the product. I also used something similar to keep contents from shifting. I had some foam pool tubes along so I placed one in the front to keep box corners from poking against the front. But this was only a precaution based on prior experience. Again this is made of durable product and. Of a good design. Due to unfamiliarity it took me 3 times as long to install on the trip out than for the return trip.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Single use only
reviews.reviewText: Since this cargo carrier is black... it gets very hot in the sun. As a result, the adhesive on the Velcro patches that hold down the zipper flap easily melts and the patches tear away.Also, the adhesive is only around the extreme outer edge of the Velcro, there isn't anything in the middle nor are they stitched or reinforced in any way.If you can use one, save your money and get a basic hardtop carrier.If you just need something cheap to throw away later... get this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This thing stayed on my little Mazda SO well. 80+mph on the free way and it didn’t budge. It rained and no water got in.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars A good value with quality issues
reviews.reviewText: Overall, I like the design and construction. It comes at a great price. But after only a few trips all of the Velcro strips that secure a lip of material over the zipper for added rain protection have come loose. Not just one or two — ALL of them. Makes me worry that something else could unexpectedly go wrong.

This is a quality, thick yet light roof top bag. Straps work well, and you can cram a lot of items inside. The zippers to the side and rear only means the front is solid so no rain comes in when driving. As well the overlapping flaps keep all rain out. There can’t be a better bag out there. This is it.

Travelled nearly 1500 kms in the car and I didnt have racks in the roof.. this bag didnt move at all and hold 2 large bags and 2 small bags and it has amazing quality. Highly recommed if you are travelling and need space in your car.
Bought it in BC and put it on our Sonic. Drove across the country in smoke, rain and sunshine... didn't move an inch. I like it.

We purchased this early July of 2020. It came in a box probably a size of men’s shoe box. We have a sedan so we purchased the junior size 10cubic. It comes with 4 straps, 4 door clips and a pull string bag for storage if your not using it.We travelled from vancouver to kelowna 5hrs in a medium rain fall. 3 washroom break in between so we checked the bag on top 3 times it didn’t moved an inch!! When we got into the cabin, the blanket on the top is damp and everything else is dry. It is wet not because of the travel but because it is raining when we are packing. It fits 5 large inflatable recliners, 2 pumps, 1king size blanket, 2 snorkling sets and 1full beach bag but we didn’t over packed it, there is still room. We put a roll of anti-slip kitchen mat to protect the car that we cut to match the size of the bag. We have a cross bar roof rack so we don’t need to use the door clips. We also purchased a rachet strap just to secure it but we didn’t end up using it cause we don’t need it. The straps that goes with it is enough.With a total of 10hrs drive, all dry, didnt moved an inch, full of dead bugs in front the bag when we got home. :-) in total, it’s perfect for us! It is boyfriend approved!Ps: step tool is recommended to pack and unpacked.

reviews.reviewTitle: Zipper is not smooth; Drove 100km/hour at times for 100km - didn't move
reviews.reviewText: made in Cambodia.The zipper is tough to zip up.works very well on a 2dr coupe.drove a total of 100km. city and hwy combined. hit 100 km/hr at times. nothing moved. just some some wind noise when i hit 80k/hourhaven't tested on the water resistant ability yet.
